# Scenario: ROAMING DENIED — u-blox SARA-R5, US-purchased Hologram SIM operating
# in China. Customer's plan/profile lacks coverage on Chinese carriers.
# Key signals:
#   +COPS=? returns Chinese networks (MCC 460) but with status 3 ("forbidden")
#   +COPS? shows the modem has selected CHN-UNICOM but as a forbidden PLMN
#   +CEREG: 0,3              (registration denied)
#   +CEER reports EMM cause 8 ("EPS services and non-EPS services not allowed")
#   +CGATT=1 -> +CME ERROR: 30
# Diagnosis: this isn't a SIM activation issue (cause 8 here is from a DIFFERENT
# context than fixture 02 — there it meant HSS hadn't propagated; here it means
# the visited network's roaming agreement with our home PLMN doesn't cover this
# subscription type or country). The classic differentiator: a fresh-activation
# cause-8 will resolve with time; a roaming-denial cause-8 will not — it requires
# a profile change.
# Customer guidance:
#   - Confirm coverage country at https://www.hologram.io/global-coverage
#   - For Hyper SIM (eUICC): activate a profile that includes China coverage.
#     With Conductor: define a geographic policy that auto-switches profiles
#     when the device crosses a country boundary.
#   - For non-eUICC SIMs: this device is going to need a different SKU for this
#     deployment — escalate to AM/CSM to scope a regional plan.

AT+CPIN?
+CPIN: READY
OK
AT+CFUN=1
OK
AT+CSQ
+CSQ: 19,99
OK
AT+COPS=?
+COPS: (3,"CHN-UNICOM","CU","46001",7),(3,"CMCC","CMCC","46000",7),,(0-4),(0,1,2)
OK
AT+COPS?
+COPS: 0,0,"CHN-UNICOM",7
OK
AT+CEREG?
+CEREG: 0,3
OK
AT+CEER
+CEER: "EMM","8","EPS services and non-EPS services not allowed"
OK
AT+CGATT=1
+CME ERROR: 30
